<p>And how people changed? Excuse me if I\'m wrong, but you haven\'t seen them in three months. Except the usual loss or gain of weight or a haircut, a person probably doesn\'t change that much. And if the person\'s a friend, even if they aren\'t, you\'ve probably seen pictures of them.</p>
<p>A fresh start? As far as I knew, first impressions carry a long, <i>long</i> time. If you\'re looking for a fresh start, I suggest you transfer to a new school. Believe me, it\'s not going to be that new of a start if you come back to the <i>same school</i> with the <i>same people</i>.</p>
<p>I\'m sure some of you did miss your friends. Your summers were jam-packed with a job, athletics, \'family time,\' summer reading, and homework (evil, evil teachers). You didn\'t get time to get out of the house much, or you were out to the point that even on your days off you were so fried that you were dead to the earth.</p>
